verbose_text: These cocaine induced slow Ca 2+ oscillations (SO) exhibited lower frequencies and broader half-widths than oscillations observed during baseline (spontaneous baseline oscillation half-width = 11.21 +/- 2.48 s; cocaine induced oscillation half-width = 24.17 +/- 3.19 s; p < 0.0001, K-S test; XREF_FIG), suggesting that cocaine SOs reflect distinct Ca 2+ sources and/or release mechanisms.
